bootlace
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a thin strip of sheep's skin with wool attached [accidentally taken off during shearing.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
